msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:14
msgid ""
"The coordinate capture plugin is easy to use and provides the ability to "
"display coordinates on the map canvas for two selected coordinate "
"reference systems (CRS)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:24
msgid ""
"Start QGIS, select |options| :guilabel:`Project Properties` from the "
":guilabel:`Settings` (KDE, Windows) or :guilabel:`File` (Gnome, macOS) "
"menu and click on the :guilabel:`Projection` tab. As an alternative, you "
"can also click on the |projectionEnabled| :sup:`CRS status` icon in the "
"lower right-hand corner of the status bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:29
msgid ""
"Click on the |checkbox| `Enable on the fly projection` checkbox and "
"select a projected coordinate system of your choice (see also "
":ref:`label_projections`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:31
msgid ""
"Activate the coordinate capture plugin in the Plugin Manager (see "
":ref:`managing_plugins`) and ensure that the dialog is visible by going "
"to :menuselection:`View --> Panels` and ensuring that |checkbox| "
":guilabel:`Coordinate Capture` is enabled. The coordinate capture dialog "
"appears as shown in Figure figure_coordinate_capture_. Alternatively, you"
" can also go to :menuselection:`Vector --> Coordinate Capture` and see if"
" |checkbox| :guilabel:`Coordinate Capture` is enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:38
msgid ""
"Click on the |geographic| :sup:`Click to the select the CRS to use for "
"coordinate display` icon and select a different CRS from the one you "
"selected above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:41
msgid ""
"To start capturing coordinates, click on **[Start capture]**. You can now"
" click anywhere on the map canvas and the plugin will show the "
"coordinates for both of your selected CRS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:44
msgid ""
"To enable mouse coordinate tracking, click the |tracking| :sup:`mouse "
"tracking` icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:46
msgid "You can also copy selected coordinates to the clipboard."
msgstr ""

